{
  "texts": [
    "Traditional control methods developed in this work (PID, LQR) might struggle to handle the complexities and dynamic changes of the system.",
    "QL and DQNL are model-free techniques that do not require explicit knowledge of the system dynamics.",
    "They can adaptively learn the control policy by interacting with the system and observing its responses, making them suitable for handling nonlinearity and instability.",
    "Furthermore, SLRIP requires continuous control actions, such as applying torque to the 1st arm to adjust the pendulum's position.",
    "Both QL and DQNL are extended to handle continuous control problems by using function approximation techniques."
  ]
}